## Phase 3 – Home & Current Weather Upgrades

### [MODIFY] [home.ts](file:///c:/Users/AkshayakumarKM/.gemini/antigravity/playground/Angular/src/app/home/home.ts) / [home.html](file:///c:/Users/AkshayakumarKM/.gemini/antigravity/playground/Angular/src/app/home/home.html) / [home.css](file:///c:/Users/AkshayakumarKM/.gemini/antigravity/playground/Angular/src/app/home/home.css)
- Render dismissable **Weather Alert banner** if `weatherData.alerts.length > 0`
- Apply a **dynamic CSS class** to `<body>` based on `conditionCode` (e.g. `bg-rainy`, `bg-sunny`) for animated background
- Add `HourlyForecastComponent`, `AqiPanelComponent`, `HistoricalChartComponent` to dashboard layout
- Subscribe to `HistoryService.add(city)` on each successful fetch
- **Favourite (⭐) button** on HomeComponent header

### [MODIFY] [current-weather.ts](file:///c:/Users/AkshayakumarKM/.gemini/antigravity/playground/Angular/src/app/components/current-weather/current-weather.ts) / [current-weather.html](file:///c:/Users/AkshayakumarKM/.gemini/antigravity/playground/Angular/src/app/components/current-weather/current-weather.html) / [current-weather.css](file:///c:/Users/AkshayakumarKM/.gemini/antigravity/playground/Angular/src/app/components/current-weather/current-weather.css)
- Subscribe to `SettingsService.unit$` — display temp in selected unit
- Replace plain temp display with **animated CSS weather icon** (pure CSS sun/rain/snow/cloud)
- Replace flat humidity/UV metrics with **SVG circular progress rings**

---

## Phase 4 – New Components

### [NEW] `src/app/components/hourly-forecast/`
- 24-hour horizontal scrollable strip
- Hour label, animated icon emoji, temperature (unit-aware), rain %
- Current hour highlighted with gold border

### [NEW] `src/app/components/aqi-panel/`
- Air Quality Index panel
- Large AQI number with colour-coded badge (green→red)
- Mini horizontal bars for PM2.5, CO₂, Ozone

### [NEW] `src/app/components/historical-chart/`
- Install `chart.js` and `ng2-charts` 
- 7-day line chart: high temp (orange) + low temp (blue) lines
- Unit-aware via SettingsService

### [NEW] `src/app/components/city-explorer/`
- Full page at `/explore`
- Card grid of all 10 cities — shows temp, condition icon, country emoji
- Click a card → navigates to `/weather/:city`
- Favourite toggle on each card

---

## Phase 5 – Routing & Geolocation

### [MODIFY] [app.routes.ts](file:///c:/Users/AkshayakumarKM/.gemini/antigravity/playground/Angular/src/app/app.routes.ts)
```typescript
{ path: 'weather/:city', component: HomeComponent },
{ path: 'explore', component: CityExplorerComponent },
{ path: '', redirectTo: 'weather/London', pathMatch: 'full' },
{ path: '**', redirectTo: 'weather/London' }
```

### [MODIFY] [home.ts](file:///c:/Users/AkshayakumarKM/.gemini/antigravity/playground/Angular/src/app/home/home.ts)
- Read `:city` param from `ActivatedRoute` on init
- When city changes via search, call `router.navigate(['/weather', city])`

### Geolocation (in [navbar.ts](file:///c:/Users/AkshayakumarKM/.gemini/antigravity/playground/Angular/src/app/navbar/navbar.ts))
- `navigator.geolocation.getCurrentPosition()` → lat/lng
- Map to nearest mock city using Euclidean distance on stored lat/lng coords

---

## Phase 6 – Accessibility

### All components
- `role`, `aria-label` on buttons, search input, compass, SVG elements
- SVG elements get `<title>` tags for screen readers
- Keyboard navigation: `keydown.ArrowDown/Up` for autocomplete dropdown

---

## Verification Plan

### Build Check
```bash
ng serve
```
- Zero console errors on all routes
- All panels render with London on `/`, `/weather/London`

### Manual Tests
1. Toggle °C ↔ °F — all temps update across all panels
2. Toggle dark ↔ light theme — persists on page reload
3. Search "Tokyo" → URL updates to `/weather/tokyo`, history chip appears
4. Star London → ⭐ shows in favourites strip, persists on reload
5. Visit `/explore` → all 10 city cards render, click one → navigates to `/weather/:city`
6. Click geolocation → nearest city loads
7. Dismiss alert banner → it disappears
